article_title: Many Hispanics eligible for Obamacare remain uninsured, federal officials say
article_text:
Hispanics have made big gains in health insurance since fall 2013

Many remain uninsured despite eligibility for financial aid

Open enrollment for ACA exchanges ends Jan. 31

article_metadata.news-keywords: Affordable Care Act, Obamacare, Latinos, Hispanics, uninsured, health insurance, open enrollment, individual mandate, young invincibles
article_metadata.description: About 4 million Hispanics have gained health insurance since fall 2013 when open enrollment first began for the Affordable Care Act’s insurance exchanges, according to the most recent reports from the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services.
